<p>The NSW Design System can be used by any department and brand classification, to provide a consistent approach to UI and UX for designers and developers. Even if you're not using the component kits, <a href="/docs/content/about/our-ecosystem.html">our ecosystem</a> allows teams to identify and use only what they require.</p>

<p>While the out-of-the-box branding reflects masterbrand corporate, the in-built theming framework can be adapted for all <a href="https://www.nsw.gov.au/branding/nsw-government-brand-framework#toc-brand-categories" target="_blank">masterbrand</a>, <a href="https://www.nsw.gov.au/branding/nsw-government-brand-framework#toc-brand-categories" target="_blank">co-brand</a> and even <a href="https://www.nsw.gov.au/branding/nsw-government-brand-framework#toc-brand-categories" target="_blank">independent</a> classification levels. <a href="https://www.nsw.gov.au/branding/nsw-government-brand-framework#toc-brand-categories" target="_blank">Endorsed</a> and <a href="https://www.nsw.gov.au/branding/nsw-government-brand-framework#toc-brand-categories" target="_blank">stand-alone</a> brand classifications can also take advantage of the pre-built base, easily adapted to their own brand identity.</p>

<h2 id="product">Product Managers</h2>
<p>Ensure your products are being built to brand, accessibility and development standards.</p>
<p>The NSW Design System:</p>
<ul>
    <li>Speeds up your design process</li>
    <li>Takes the burden of accessibility compliance off you (WCAG 2.2 AA)</li>
    <li>Ensures you're following NSW Government branding</li>
    <li>Enables your designers and developers to work off a common base</li>
</ul>
<p>Our pre-built kits:</p>
<ul>
    <li>Make your digital products responsive for mobile, tablet, and desktop</li>
    <li>Dramatically speed up your development process</li>
    <li>Allow you to share components with other design system users</li>
</ul>


